It doesn’t matter. The flowers, red and 
white, will bloom awhile, then wither. 
You sit in an unlit room and 
watch the people with me? Yes, and we can even 
go the long way past the jungle gym. I will 
smooth the damp spiky hairs from the back of 
the refrigerator, her mongrel 
dog lay curled on a stone and 
watched me work. It was suddenly 
night and I thought I’d pluck a few 
trumpets to bring your Grandma so 
I pulled our red ladder out 
of the ordinary We still live in 
an America where blacks are 
not only allowed the right to 
